JOHANNESBURG - June 20 is World Refugee Day but 2016/7 hasn't been kind to those forced out of their homes around the world.Devastating conflicts, violence and persecution in Syria, South Sudan and elsewhere have left a record 65.6 million people displaced by the end of last year, according to the United Nations.Children caught up in the refugee crises are front and centre to one Johannesburg school.Sacred Heart College in Observatory is running an education project for children of refugees.Click on the above video to hear Head of the College Colin Northmore, share more about their project.eNCA